README.md
     1→# dotenv
     5→Dotenv is a zero-dependency module that loads environment variables from a `.env` file into [`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env). Storing configuration in the environment separate from code is based on [The Twelve-Factor App](https://12factor.net/config) methodology.
     6→
     7→[Watch the tutorial](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtkZR0NFd1g)
     8→
     9→&nbsp;
    10→
    11→## Usage
    13→Install it.
    14→
    15→```sh
    16→npm install dotenv --save
    17→```
    18→
    19→Create a `.env` file in the root of your project:
    20→
    21→```ini
    22→# .env
    23→S3_BUCKET="YOURS3BUCKET"
    24→SECRET_KEY="YOURSECRETKEYGOESHERE"
      →…
    39→## Advanced
    43→Import with [ES6](#how-do-i-use-dotenv-with-import):
    44→
    45→```javascript
    46→import 'dotenv/config'
    47→```
    48→
    49→ES6 import if you need to set config options:
    50→
    51→```javascript
    52→import dotenv from 'dotenv'
    53→dotenv.config({ path: '/custom/path/to/.env' })
    54→```
